					<div id="pnlCataracts">
						<h2>Cataracts</h2>
						<p>Cataracts occur when the lens of the eye becomes cloudy, and are often treated with surgery.</p>
					</div>
					<div id="pnlGlare">
						<h2>Glare</h2>
						<p>Glare results from excessive visible light. It can be distracting or even dangerous, and can occur day or night. Photochromic lenses with anti-reflective coating reduce more kinds of glare than any other lens.</p>
					</div>
					<div id="pnlGlaucoma">
						<h2>Glaucoma</h2>
						<p>Glaucoma can cause headaches, blurred vision, difficulty adapting to darkness, haloes around lights, or no symptoms. Early diagnostics and treatment can help prevent vision loss</p>
					</div>
					<div id="pnlPresbyopia">
						<h2>Presbyopia</h2>
						<p>Presbyopia is an inevitable, age-related condition that makes reading and seeing close-up difficult. It can be treated with proper eye wear, like progressive lenses or bifocals.</p>
					</div>
					<div id="pnlDiabetic">
						<h2>Diabetic Retinopaty</h2>
						<p>Diabetic retinopathy results in broken, leaking or blocked blood vessels in the retina that impair vision over time. Early treatment can slow progression.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div id="pnlOptimize">
					<h2 id="hOptimizeToday">Optimize your sight today.</h2>
					<p>Having Healthy Sight is about more than seeing &ldquo;20/20&rdquo; on an eye chart. It&rsquo;s about understanding how to get the very best quality of vision today, and taking the steps necessary to preserve eye health and well-being for the future.</p>
				</div>
				<div id="pnlPreserve">
					<h2 id="hPreserveTomorrow">Preserve your sight for tomorrow.</h2>
					<p>Learn the simple steps that can be taken to enhance and protect vision, and find out what you can do to get involved with the Transitions<sup>&reg;</sup> Healthy Sight for Life Fund to help bring this important message to others.</p>
				</div>
